# Beelectric multi-app context

This codebase is **one of three apps** in the Beelectric CMMS ecosystem. Keep API, schema, and conventions in sync with the others.

## The three apps

| App | Stack | Role |
|-----|--------|-----|
| **This repo** (beelectric-react) | React/Next.js, Turborepo | Admin / back-office web app |
| **Technician app** | Flutter | Field technicians (another Cursor project) |
| **Requestor app** | Flutter | Requestors (another Cursor project) |

## Shared backend

- **Supabase** is the single backend for all three apps (auth, DB, RLS, Realtime).
- Schema and RLS are defined in this repo under `supabase/` (migrations, types, policies).
- Any change to tables, RLS, or auth that affects mobile apps must stay consistent; document in `docs/MULTI-APP-CONTEXT.md` when relevant.

## Keeping in sync

- When changing Supabase schema, RLS, or API contracts, consider impact on the Flutter technician and requestor apps.
- Shared context for **both Cursor projects** is in `docs/MULTI-APP-CONTEXT.md`. The Flutter project should have the same (or a copy) of that doc so the AI there knows about this React app and the shared backend.
- Env: all apps use the same Supabase URL and anon key (from `.env.example` / equivalent in each app).
